==English==

===Etymology===
Irish [[ollamh#Irish|ollamh]], from Old Irish [[ollam]] ‘doctor’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ɒlæv/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|ollav|ollavs}}
# in Irish history, a man of [[science]] or [[learning]], equivalent to a university professor
#:*'''1922''': Glittereyed, his rufous skull close to his greencapped desklamp sought the face, bearded amid darkgreener shadow, an '''ollav''', holyeyed. — James Joyce, ''Ulysses''

